given array, find bitwise xor of the values of all possible subarray of array

For an array: arr = [1, 2, 3]
All subarrays are:

[1]       -> 1
[1,2]     -> 1^2 = 3
[1,2,3]   -> 1^2^3 = 0
[2]       -> 2
[2,3]     -> 2^3 = 1
[3]       -> 3

Now XOR all these values: 1 ^ 3 ^ 0 ^ 2 ^ 1 ^ 3 = 2

Each element contributes to several subarrays.
Element arr[i] appears in: (i + 1) * (n - i)
subarrays.
If this count is:
    even → XOR cancels out
    odd → remains in final answer

So only elements appearing odd number of times matter.\

An element contributes only when: (i + 1) * (n - i) is odd
This happens only when:
  n is odd
  and i is even

So:
    If array length is even → answer is 0
    If odd → XOR all elements at even indices

public class Main {

    static int xorOfAllSubarrayXors(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;

        // If length is even
        if (n % 2 == 0)
            return 0;

        int xor = 0;

        // XOR elements at even index
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i += 2) {
            xor ^= arr[i];
        }

        return xor;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3};

        System.out.println(xorOfAllSubarrayXors(arr));
    }
}
